 Let $\omega = e^{i \pi/3}$. Then $\omega^3 = e^{i \pi} = -1$, so $\omega^3 + 1 = 0$, which factors as \[(\omega + 1)(\omega^2 - \omega + 1) = 0.\]Since $\omega \neq -1$, we have that $\omega^2 - \omega + 1 = 0$.
